body:
We have a cow that rams into people and scream &quot;You can&#039;t milk these!&quot; {{champion:12}} 

We have a frozen bird that creates localized blizzards, dies and hatches from an ice egg, and does the chicken dance. {{champion:34}} 

We have a birdman whom was once the emperor to a once great empire, and keeps stealing sandbox after sandbox from children. {{champion:268}} 

We have a fish thingy that I&#039;m pretty sure pole dances in lane all day and has a pet shark of which he feeds small children to. {{champion:105}} 

We have a dog that has learned to farm and found that he actually enjoys it. {{champion:75}} 

We have an armadillo who vocabulary linguistics are limited to &quot;OK&quot; {{champion:33}} 

We have a crocodile that bears immense rage for his brother, which is for some reason an entirely different species. {{champion:58}} 

We have a cat that is missing one eye and has taken to hunting everything he can find. {{champion:107}} 

We have a scorpion made of stone and crystal that drags people screaming into his den to &quot;feel his sting&quot;. {{champion:72}} 

We have a catfish that enjoys eating people and spitting them back up so that he can eat them again. {{champion:223}} 

We have a rat that steals things and poisons people, while enjoying the occasional cupcake. {{champion:29}} 

We have a lightning bear that likes to run at people and toss them over his shoulder. {{champion:106}} 

We have a wolf that actually killed off one of the champions in the game, and occasionally wears their skin into battle, while at other times dresses up like and old granny. {{champion:19}} 

And we have a monkey that learned martial arts from master yi and enjoys the occasional banana from time to time. {{champion:62}} 

Maybe it&#039;s time we had an acrobatic turtle!
